<Base title="Privacy Policy — The Yips" description="Privacy policy for The Yips golf stats app.">
  <main style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem; font-family: Inter, sans-serif; color: #e5e5e5; line-height: 1.7;">
    <a href="/" style="color: #4ADE80; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;">← Back to The Yips</a>

    <h1 style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #ffffff; font-size: 2rem;">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p style="color: #9ca3af; font-size: 0.9rem;">Effective date: July 2, 2026</p>

    <p>The Yips is a golf stats tracker built for golfers who want to understand and improve their game. This policy explains what data the app collects, how it's used, and your rights around it.</p>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">What We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information</strong> — your name and email address when you sign in with Google or Apple.</li>
      <li><strong>Golf data</strong> — rounds, scores, hole-by-hole stats, shot distances, club selections, and course information you enter or record in the app.</li>
      <li><strong>Location data</strong> — GPS coordinates captured during a round to measure shot distances and record green locations. Location is only accessed when you actively use shot-tracking features.</li>
      <li><strong>Device information</strong> — basic device identifiers used for authentication and app functionality.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">How We Use It</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide the app's core features: round tracking, strokes gained analysis, and club performance stats.</li>
      <li>To sync your data across devices via The Yips API (our backend, hosted in the United States).</li>
      <li>To calculate your handicap differential and strokes gained metrics.</li>
      <li>To improve the app based on aggregate, anonymized usage patterns.</li>
      <li>To train and improve the AI Caddy feature using anonymized shot, distance, and club data. This data is stripped of all personally identifiable information before use.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your data. We do not use your golf data for advertising.</p>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">Third-Party Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Sign-In</strong> — used for authentication. Subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" style="color: #4ADE80;">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Apple Sign-In</strong> — used for authentication on iOS. Subject to <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" style="color: #4ADE80;">Apple's Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Your data is retained as long as your account is active. You can request deletion of your account and all associated data at any time by contacting us.</p>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You can request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data at any time. To do so, email us at the address below.</p>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">Children</h2>
    <p>The Yips is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13.</p>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy as the app evolves. Material changes will be noted with an updated effective date at the top of this page.</p>

    <h2 style="color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2rem;">Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions? Email us at <a href="mailto:mitch@undeadops.dev" style="color: #4ADE80;">mitch@undeadops.dev</a></p>
  </main>
</Base>
